From 31c9b1188b69da372f638b93d48e2322046e3f16 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arnaud Rebillout <arnaudr@debian.org>
Date: Sun, 23 Nov 2025 12:41:54 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] hydra-gtk: Rename INSTALL to README-autoconf

INSTALL is a file generated by autoreconf, so we can't at the same time
have it committed to the repo, and have it regenerated each time when
xhydra is built: depending on the version of autoreconf, the file is
different, so there's a git diff to deal with.

In order to keep the file around (in case it's useful), rename it to
README-autoconf.
---
 .gitignore                             | 1 +
 hydra-gtk/{INSTALL => README-autoconf} | 0
 2 files changed, 1 insertion(+)
 rename hydra-gtk/{INSTALL => README-autoconf} (100%)

diff --git a/.gitignore b/.gitignore
index 79b20660..b27da2b4 100644
--- a/.gitignore
+++ b/.gitignore
@@ -7,6 +7,7 @@ hydra.exe
 hydra.restore
 xhydra
 xhydra.exe
+hydra-gtk/INSTALL
 hydra-gtk/Makefile.in
 hydra-gtk/aclocal.m4
 hydra-gtk/autom4te.cache/
diff --git a/hydra-gtk/INSTALL b/hydra-gtk/README-autoconf
similarity index 100%
rename from hydra-gtk/INSTALL
rename to hydra-gtk/README-autoconf
